A borrowed plume to crown my timid brow;
This transformation lends me fleeting grace,
Though time demands its treasures back somehow.

Now home, my **bedroom** mirrors strange disguise,
Where sequins gleam on unfamiliar forms;
We stitch ourselves with temporary lies
Before the night's expected gathering storms.

But dawn will strip these vibrant second skins -
The rented self departs; true life begins.

